31
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:30,990
=Love is Always Online=

32
00:01:31,020 --> 00:01:33,940
=Episode 34=

33
00:01:34,380 --> 00:01:36,520
Before you become the successor,

34
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,840
there are many areas
where you need to improve.

35
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:40,640
But,

36
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:42,440
something like this

37
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:46,120
isn't where you need to improve.

38
00:01:46,860 --> 00:01:47,800
Exactly.

39
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:50,200
Look at the children
of the Huangfu family.

40
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:52,320
They've been studying abroad,

41
00:01:52,620 --> 00:01:55,240
and now they've earned another degree
in business management.

42
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:56,480
That's really impressive.

43
00:01:57,940 --> 00:01:59,080
But how many people

44
00:01:59,780 --> 00:02:01,000
actually understand this wine?

45
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:04,280
Studying business is the path to success

46
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,720
and financial prosperity.

47
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:09,940
But Ancheng wants to do
something he likes.

48
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:12,040
Making money isn't
the only thing that matters.

49
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,060
Grandpa,

50
00:02:15,060 --> 00:02:16,100
Dad,

51
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:17,060
Aunt and Uncle,

52
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:18,000
you're right.

53
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:19,440
I get it.

54
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:21,420
Ancheng.

55
00:02:21,420 --> 00:02:22,600
We just want the best for you.

56
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:24,960
We hope you don't waste your time

57
00:02:25,220 --> 00:02:26,160
and focus on your studies.

58
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:29,520
I do believe in you.

59
00:02:29,860 --> 00:02:30,800
Keep it up.

60
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:33,620
Alright, enough talk. Let's eat.

61
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:36,070
Come on, come on.

62
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,230
Here, have a drink.

63
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:57,440
Ancheng.

64
00:02:57,620 --> 00:02:58,840
I've always wanted to ask you,

65
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:00,880
why did you stop chasing your dream?

66
00:03:02,980 --> 00:03:04,160
Actually, many times,

67
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:06,320
I wanted to drop everything
and go to France.

68
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:08,520
But what if I failed?

69
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:11,220
Grandpa was right.

70
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:13,550
I should manage the family business.

71
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,020
The Jiang family's years of hard work

72
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:17,200
can't be ruined on our watch.

73
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:20,160
That's why I envy you.

74
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:22,800
You can chase your dreams
without holding back.

75
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,740
Staying home probably
takes even more courage.

76
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,230
So many eyes are watching.

77
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:29,720
If you do well, it's expected.
If not, you get criticized.

78
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,450
So I finally understood.

79
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,580
I can't choose where I was born,

80
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:34,820
but at least I have the right

81
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:35,940
to decide my own path.

82
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:38,880
Unlike me, worrying too much,

83
00:03:39,350 --> 00:03:40,750
and ending up doing nothing well.

84
00:03:41,060 --> 00:03:42,740
Why don't you trust yourself, Ancheng?

85
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,420
Actually,

86
00:03:45,140 --> 00:03:46,780
when I learned about
Yao Yuan's background,

87
00:03:47,340 --> 00:03:48,500
I wanted to tell you.

88
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:51,790
It was me who recommended
to pull funding

89
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:54,660
from Yao Yuan's parents.

90
00:03:55,620 --> 00:03:56,700
I just never expected that

91
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,220
would've gotten them killed.

92
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:03,580
Actually, back at Jiulong,

93
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:05,580
after I clashed with Chen,

94
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:07,900
I indirectly figured out it was you.

95
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:11,380
Then why aren't you mad at me?

96
00:04:11,740 --> 00:04:12,660
I was mad,

97
00:04:13,460 --> 00:04:15,420
so mad I wanted to come find you.

98
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:17,060
But...

99
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,500
Hey,

100
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:22,100
Jiang Ancheng was pretty smug
in the meeting today.

101
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:25,140
You know,

102
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,140
if he weren't Chairman Jiang's kid,

103
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:30,180
would he sway investment that much?

104
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:32,700
Don't worry.

105
00:04:33,020 --> 00:04:34,940
This world is brutally practical.

106
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:37,980
No strength means you're out.

107
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:39,500
With that project,

108
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,340
just the personnel costs
have already gone over budget.

109
00:04:44,140 --> 00:04:45,260
Just wait and watch the show.

110
00:04:45,850 --> 00:04:47,430
He's poison, we're the sugar.

111
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,580
Take him down...

112
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:50,820
So Jiulong has two rotten apples.

113
00:04:54,020 --> 00:04:54,980
Keep talking.

114
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:55,900
Why are you suddenly quiet?

115
00:04:56,980 --> 00:04:58,420
We were just joking around.

116
00:04:58,420 --> 00:05:01,140
Talking behind backs
but chickening out face to face.

117
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:02,740
Just joking?

118
00:05:03,260 --> 00:05:04,120
Should I get my brother

119
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,220
to come over

120
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:06,900
and joke with you?

121
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:07,740
Well,

122
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:09,780
that's not necessary.

123
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:11,700
Take back everything

124
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:12,980
you said earlier.

125
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,700
If I hear even a whisper again,

126
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:16,900
just try me.

127
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,240
Yes, yes.

128
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:23,500
Why didn't you tell me?

129
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:26,180
I just realized how much pressure
you were under.

130
00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:27,900
I really felt sorry for you.

131
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:30,300
You didn't do anything wrong.

132
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:33,140
Based on the data,
that was the right decision.

133
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:36,260
But I never believed
numbers tell the whole story.

134
00:05:36,980 --> 00:05:38,390
I trust more in the power of people.

135
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:40,210
Everyone makes mistakes.

136
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:43,160
But fixing them the right way

137
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:44,780
is what counts.

138
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,420
Now I finally get

139
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:50,260
why Dad always liked you.

140
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:52,980
This position really belongs to you.

141
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:55,980
Ancheng,

142
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:56,900
don't say that.

143
00:05:57,590 --> 00:05:59,780
I'm not making excuses
or trying to please you.

144
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,100
First,

145
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:02,180
no one knows Jiulong's affairs

146
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,620
better than you,

147
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:05,060
be it big or small.

148
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:06,420
Second,

149
00:06:06,420 --> 00:06:08,020
Dad always said Jiulong needs change,

150
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:11,020
but he didn't see you were
already making it happen.

151
00:06:12,700 --> 00:06:14,020
You may focus on results,

152
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:17,780
but you truly understand
every single employee.

153
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,420
A good leader

154
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:21,660
should know how to bring out

155
00:06:21,660 --> 00:06:22,900
the team's greatest strengths.

156
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:25,780
But Dad doesn't see it that way.

157
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:29,220
He just hasn't noticed yet.

158
00:06:30,020 --> 00:06:31,500
Time will prove everything.

159
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,740
No one is better suited
for this position than you.

160
00:06:37,020 --> 00:06:37,940
Anlan.

161
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:39,460
Thanks.

162
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:41,340
What are you thanking me for?

163
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:46,860
Vice President,

164
00:06:46,860 --> 00:06:47,940
the meeting is about to start.

165
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,180
I still have a meeting to attend.
Gotta go.

166
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,020
Get some rest.

167
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:54,300
Okay.

168
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:08,140
Ancheng,

169
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,540
Wang Xing has made many calls,

170
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,340
demanding the lawsuit be dropped.

171
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:13,460
Just ignore him.

172
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:16,460
I think in situations like this,

173
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:17,940
it's best to let things blow over.

174
00:07:18,390 --> 00:07:19,260
Look,

175
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:20,780
if you insist on taking legal action,

176
00:07:20,780 --> 00:07:23,260
it'll only bring more trouble
for you and the company.

177
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,500
I say we just drop it.

178
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:29,660
If we let Wang Xing slide this time,

179
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:31,300
he'll just push his luck further.

180
00:07:32,860 --> 00:07:33,780
This matter

181
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:35,340
is non-negotiable.

182
00:08:18,020 --> 00:08:19,020
I'm here.

183
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,700
What food did you bring today?

184
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,940
You'll know once you try it.

185
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:28,940
Feeling better?

186
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:29,860
Much better.

187
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:40,900
Such a hassle.

188
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:55,300
So, how is it?

189
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:56,580
Does it taste bad?

190
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,820
I didn't expect Mrs. Jiang to be

191
00:09:01,820 --> 00:09:03,100
such a great cook.

192
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:08,060
I've been practicing at home these days.

193
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:09,540
I've failed so many times.

194
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:12,140
I had Xinran and Wen Cheng
try my dishes.

195
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:13,580
They both ended up gaining weight.

196
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:16,740
You even added goji berries.

197
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,180
Pretty tasty, right?

198
00:09:18,180 --> 00:09:19,700
Next time, don't bother cooking.

199
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:20,780
I'll take you to eat out.

200
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:21,900
That won't work.

201
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,020
You're not fully recovered.

202
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:25,020
Food outside is too greasy.
You shouldn't eat it now.

203
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:28,180
Seeing you makes me feel better already.

204
00:09:28,180 --> 00:09:29,460
The doctor said I can be discharged.

205
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:30,940
Then eat a little more.

206
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:32,300
Don't make me carry you home.

207
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,420
Mm.

208
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:48,980
I should've never come.

209
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,220
You win.

210
00:09:50,420 --> 00:09:51,380
Giving up so soon?

211
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:56,580
How did your skills get so much worse?

212
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:59,860
Why take a simple game so seriously?

213
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:02,700
I've been busy lately
with the gym expansion.

214
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:04,140
When would I have time for this?

215
00:10:04,580 --> 00:10:06,420
Since you're the gym's boss,

216
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:07,480
shouldn't you be training more?

217
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,860
Come on, I'm the boss,
not the coach, okay?

218
00:10:11,860 --> 00:10:12,780
Oh, right,

219
00:10:13,140 --> 00:10:15,140
your company is reviewing my project.

220
00:10:15,140 --> 00:10:17,540
Isn't this taking a bit too long?

221
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:19,460
That's just the standard process.

222
00:10:20,780 --> 00:10:22,220
But aren't those rules made by people?

223
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:24,020
Chen said,

224
00:10:24,020 --> 00:10:25,420
since we're friends,

225
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:26,260
he'd help me

226
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:27,700
and make it pass soon.

227
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:29,300
What does that mean?

228
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:32,620
It's so hot.

229
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:34,140
Allen,

230
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,660
Jiulong has connections
with many partners.

231
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:39,060
Mixing personal and work matters

232
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:40,460
makes it hard to get things right.

233
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:42,180
I know.

234
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,620
I know you've always

235
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:44,780
handled things fairly.

236
00:10:44,780 --> 00:10:45,700
But,

237
00:10:45,980 --> 00:10:48,420
Chen just helped out a little,
it's no big deal.

238
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:49,740
Do you want me to ask him directly?

239
00:10:51,460 --> 00:10:53,620
Alright, alright, I'll just tell you.

240
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,020
We just slightly enhanced

241
00:10:56,540 --> 00:10:58,820
the expected performance of the project.

242
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:00,380
It's not like

243
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:01,820
it won't be met.

244
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:19,820
Maggie,

245
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,580
give me the approval form
and documents for Yuanfang Resort.

246
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:38,300
Vice President.

247
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:50,020
Yuanfang Resort is
a major investment case

248
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:50,940
for Fang Corporation.

249
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:52,180
Is this all we have?

250
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:54,060
Yes.

251
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:54,980
That's all.

252
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:00,700
This resort

253
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:02,660
has a big gap from
the expected return on investment.

254
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:05,260
Although you later caught up
on the payback period,

255
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:07,380
your initial assessment

256
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:08,380
was way off, why is that?

257
00:12:10,060 --> 00:12:11,020
Because

258
00:12:12,220 --> 00:12:13,140
at the time,

259
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:14,500
Chen specifically instructed me

260
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,060
that Mr. Fang and Chairman Jiang

261
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:17,580
have a very close relationship,

262
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:19,740
and you're also close with Miss Fang.

263
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,660
So he handed this case over to him.

264
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:23,740
After that, I did

265
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:25,820
the risk assessment based on the data
and financial reports

266
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:27,100
Chen provided me.

267
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:31,420
Got it.

268
00:12:31,420 --> 00:12:32,340
You can go now.

269
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:50,860
You're so weak right now.

270
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,060
Get better soon,

271
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,660
or we'd have to take care of you.

272
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,740
It's really good to be home.

273
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:00,340
You know what?

274
00:13:00,660 --> 00:13:02,460
I wasn't just missing you
while I was there.

275
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:04,260
I was missing my king-size bed too.

276
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:06,540
But now it's all good.

277
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:09,340
The bed's here, and so are you.

278
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:11,660
I'm about to get better in no time.

279
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:13,780
I'll take you to

280
00:13:13,780 --> 00:13:14,780
your king-size bed now.

281
00:13:14,780 --> 00:13:15,700
Let's go.

282
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,220
Feeling dizzy.

283
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:23,660
Take it slow.

284
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,060
I'll get you water.

